The paper focuses on creating a new framework for dense SLAM that is light enough for micro-robot systems based on depth camera and inertial sensor. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses feature-based and direct methods in visual SLAM, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed framework involves utilizing Fourier transformation for data association, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of an attitude and heading reference system (AHRS) and axonometric projection, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
